correctness.rationale: Largely incorrect and schema-violating. Multiple required numeric fields are null (schema disallows): pressure.quantityValue.numericValue, nucleationPeriod.quantityValue.numericValue, dosingTime[*].precursor/coReactant.numericValue, purgeTime[*].precursor/coReactant.numericValue, flowRates[*].precursorFlow/coReactantFlow/purgingGasFlow.numericValue, uniformity.variation.numericValue, conformality.aspectRatio.numericValue, filmComposition.elementalConcentration.values.quantityValue.numericValue, roughness.value.quantityValue.numericValue, electricalProperties values. Key factual errors: (1) thicknessControl.filmThickness set to 60 nm with 600 cycles and GPC=0.1 Å for all compounds—none are reported and contradict the article (devices use 5 nm IGO on 5 nm ZnO; XRD comparisons use 20 nm IGO; ZnO SCL is 5 nm; no 60 nm film). (2) supercycleDesign is wrong: sequence ['In2O3','Ga2O3','ZnO'] with 1:1:1 counts is not reported; ZnO is a separate SCL, and the IGO supercycle uses In:Ga subcycles of In-only, 6:1, 4:1, 2:1 (Fig. S6). (3) materialProperties.crystallinity set to polycrystalline, but the process tied to the reported device metrics (μ_FE=95.5 cm2/Vs, V_TH=1.33 V) corresponds to highly ordered crystalline bixbyite (222) IGO on ZnO/θ-Al2O3 (GI-WAXD/TEM/XRD). (4) filmComposition.atomicRatio incorrectly includes Zn; the channel film is In–Ga–O only; compositions such as In2O3, In1.8Ga0.2O3, In1.7Ga0.3O3, In1.4Ga0.6O3 are reported (XRF). (5) Roughness is reported (rms 0.34–0.37 nm) but left empty. (6) Carrier/purging gas set to Ar is not explicitly stated (only O2/[Ar+O2] mixture fraction reported); treat as unsubstantiated. Correct values to use: precursors (DATI, TMG; DEZ) and co-reactant (O2 plasma) and PEALD temperature (250 °C) and plasma power (100 W) are correct; device properties match. To fix: remove/replace nulls with reported numbers; set film thickness to the reported values (e.g., IGO 5 nm on ZnO 5 nm for devices or 20 nm for XRD studies); correct supercycle (In:Ga subcycle counts of 6:1, 4:1, 2:1; exclude ZnO from supercycle); set crystallinity to highly ordered bixbyite (222) for SCL-assisted films; restrict atomicRatio elements to In and Ga; populate roughness with 0.34–0.37 nm and note XRF as composition method.

completeness.rationale: The extraction is largely incomplete and partly incorrect relative to both the article and the schema. Major issues: (1) Multiple processes are described in the paper but only one process is provided and it conflates conditions: ho In2−xGaxO3 grown on ZnO/θ‑Al2O3 and rp In2−xGaxO3 grown directly on θ‑Al2O3 should be separate processes. (2) Missing ALD step for the θ‑Al2O3 seed layer (PEALD at 150 °C, O2 plasma 50 W, TMA) although it is central to the growth; Al2O3 is absent from aldSystem and reactantSelection. (3) Numerous schema-required numeric fields are null or placeholders: pressure.numericValue, dosingTime/purgeTime/flowRates numericValues, nucleationPeriod, optical/electrical properties, uniformity.variation, conformality.aspectRatio, roughness.value, filmDensity.value—these violate the no-null requirement and are not traceable. (4) Several values are invented or inconsistent with the article: growth-per-cycle (0.1 Å) and number of cycles (600) not reported; filmThickness set to 60 nm while the article reports 5 nm channels (devices) and 20 nm films (XRD), ZnO SCL 5 nm, Al2O3 30 nm. (5) supercycleDesign is incorrect: ZnO is not part of the In–Ga supercycle; counts should reflect reported In/Ga subcycle ratios (In-only, 6/1, 4/1, 2/1). (6) reactantSelection carrierGas and purgingGas are set to Ar without citation; only the plasma gas mixture (O2/[Ar+O2]) and O2 fraction are provided. (7) materialProperties.crystallinity is set to “polycrystalline” while the device metrics given (μFE 95.5 cm2 V−1 s−1, VTH 1.33 V, SS 166 mV/dec, ION/IOFF ≈ 1e8) correspond to the highly ordered (222) films; atomicRatio wrongly includes Zn (the film is In–Ga–O). To improve: add a second process for rp growth; add the Al2O3 SCL deposition with TMA/O2 plasma details; correct film thicknesses (Al2O3 30 nm, ZnO 5 nm, IGO 5 nm for devices, 20 nm for XRD runs); fix supercycle counts (In/Ga = 6/1, 4/1, 2/1); set crystallinity appropriately per process; populate roughness (~0.34–0.37 nm, AFM); remove uninformed carrier/purge gas or justify; and avoid nulls, replacing only with article-backed values. Overall, the extraction does not meet schema completeness or factual traceability.
